Field Label: Was 0.3 to 0.8 milliliters of serum collected in a red-top or gel-barrier tube?
Was the sample is stable for 14 days at room temperature, refrigerated or frozen?
Was the sample incubated with biotinylated and ruthenium labeled monoclonal TSH-specific antibodies to form a sandwich complex?
Were the results measured against a calibration curve?
What is the repeatability and coefficients of variation of the assay?
